
Uninstall MongoDB Community Edition
Step 1		:  Stop the mongod process 

venkata@krv-dev-mongo:~#  sudo service mongod stop

Step 2		:  Remove any MongoDB packages that you had previously installed.

venkata@krv-dev-mongo:~#  sudo apt-get purge mongodb-org*

Step 3		:  Remove MongoDB databases and log files.

venkata@krv-dev-mongo:~#  sudo rm -r /var/log/mongodb
venkata@krv-dev-mongo:~#  sudo rm -r /var/lib/mongodb
